    <id>nirsoft-ntfslinksview.portable</id>
    <title>NTFSLinksView (Portable)</title>
    <version>1.35</version>
    <authors>NirSoft</authors>
    <owners>WetHat</owners>
    <summary>
        Shows a list of all symbolic links and junctions in the specified folder, and their target paths.
    </summary>
    <description>
        Starting from Windows Vista, Microsoft uses symbolic links and junction points of NTFS file system
        in order to make changes in the folders structure of Windows and keep the compatibility of
        applications written for older versions of Windows. This utility simply shows you a list of all
        symbolic links and junctions in the specified folder, and their target paths. It also allows you
        to save the symbolic links/junctions list into text/html/xml/csv file.
    </description>
    <projectUrl>https://www.nirsoft.net/utils/ntfs_links_view.html</projectUrl>
